[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Graph Data and Sources . . .[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The data for the graphs is taken from various Government or Local Authority sources, including . . .
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Glossary / Acronyms. . .[bold]&#xa0;[bold]AD : Anaerobic Digestion[bold] – a technique for dealing with the Biodegradable/Putrescible waste.
[normal]IVC : In-Vessel Composting[bold] – composting process carried out in closed containers.
[normal]LACW : Local Authority Collected Waste[bold] – the new
[normal]er, broader definition of Local Authority waste.
[normal]MSW : Municipal Solid Waste[bold] – the original term used for most of the waste collected by Councils.
[normal]MRF : Materials Reclamation Facility[bold] – used to separate the various materials fractions in waste.
[normal]MBT :[bold] 
[normal]Mecha[bold]nical and Biological Treatment[bold] - processes used to both separate and treat waste.
[normal]H&amp;W :[bold] 
[normal]Herefordshire County Council and Worcestershire County Council. [bold](also HCC &amp; WCC)
[normal]Mercia[bold] : [bold]Mercia[bold] Waste Management[bold] – the PFI Contractor to the two Councils.
[normal]C&amp;I Waste: [bold]Commercial and Industrial[bold] waste – over 70% of this is already being recycled.
[normal]WRAP : Waste and Resources Action Programme[bold].[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Additional Notes/Comments on specific Graphs in the text of the report . . .[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Graph 1:  H&amp;W PFI Actual and Predicted Cost – [bold]Annual Charge . . .[bold]This shows H&amp;W PFI Unitary Charge payments paid to the Contractor so far, as recorded by HM Treasury to date. The costs have then been projected forward to the Contract end. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Comment:[bold]  These figures are the gross Payments made, but 
[normal]do [bold]not include[bold] 
[normal]the additional cost[bold] that will be added by financing, constructing, and then running the proposed Incinerator.
